      "side": 1,
      "message": "I understand that this code is directly from MSDN, but that doesn\u0027t make it better. We should only call the API for the second time if it failed for the first time. Otherwise we\u0027re potentially hanging for extra milliseconds/seconds here if there\u0027s some networking issue and Windows waits for a timeout again.\nP.S. MSDN sample code isn\u0027t really something one should to copy and reuse - it\u0027s usually student contractors who write those, and some API samples are plain wrong, e.g. http://osherove.com/blog/2005/7/11/fixing-msdns-bad-dpapi-examples-and-whats-dpapi-anyway.html",
      "range": {
